 1. Sidebar shows My Day, then a PROJECTS section with top 5 projects, then Archive and Templates
  2. More expands to show all projects inline, Less collapses to top 5
  3. Clicking a project loads its tasks in the main view with the project name as title
  4. Project nav items show color dot, name, and task count badge
  5. Project order is configurable via drag-and-drop in Settings > Projects using @dnd-kit
  6. Project order persists to database via sidebar_order field
  7. Cmd+2 opens project view with topmost project selected
  8. Tab/Shift+Tab cycles through projects when in project view
  9. Each project remembers its list/kanban layout preference (persisted in settings table)
  10. Cmd+L toggles and saves layout per project
  11. My Day groups tasks by project first, then by status within each project
  12. Each project group in My Day has a project name header with project color
  13. My Day label filter aggregates labels from all projects with tasks in My Day
  14. My Day add-task input has an inline project selector dropdown defaulting to default project
  15. Backlog view and ProjectSwitcher component are fully removed
  16. Cmd+1 = My Day, Cmd+2 = Projects, Cmd+3 = Archive, Cmd+4 = Templates
  17. Database migration adds sidebar_order to projects table
